I"­<p><strong>Romantic Melodrama: Feeling in Search of Form</strong> is a four-year British Academy-funded project that will document every performance of melodrama in Britain before 1843. Taking its cues from early responses, where audiences experienced melodramaâ€™s powerful stage effects and highly wrought scenes of suspense as a sort of augmented reality, the project explores how the formâ€™s techniques (such as continuous music, extensive pantomime, and immersive soundscapes) created a new theatre of sensation that heightened the affective experiences of audiences. Finally, the research tracks how these same techniques also impacted writers working in other printed genres and media, repositioning melodramaâ€“and theatrical performance more generallyâ€“as an exemplary and revealing form in Romantic culture.</p>

